This retro-style jelly mould card evokes memories of proper parties with jelly and ice cream. Those nostalgic afternoons of pass the parcel and pin the tail on the donkey. What fun!

Screenprinted by hand in a selection of our own-mix colours. Each card comes with a contarasting coloured envelope.

Blank inside for your personal Happy Birthday message.

Made from Italian Fabriano heavyweight paper.

The folded card is size A6. 10.5 x 15 cm

A typographic treat of book genres on one side; Crime, science fiction, humour, romance, horror.  On the other side: books, books, books.

Screenprinted by hand in the Mr.PS studio here in the UK. This bag is also available in grey - see separate listing.
 
100% heavy weight cotton canvas, with strong long handles.

Dimensions: 48x36cm with a 60cm handles. Hand-wash. (minimal shrinkage first time.)

Free UK p&p

Also available in turquoise, see separate listing.

Free UK p&p

Fish & chips for tea - yeah!

name: One Lump or Two screenprint on paper -mint/mauve
description:

This is one of an open edition series of screenprints. As they are all hand-printed by me, they are all a little tiny bit individual.

Free UK p&p

name: Pack of 5 screenprinted greeting cards
description:
Get organised, save money, and be prepared for any celebration or message-sending necessity with a pack of 5 assorted cards.

Available in two different combinations of Mr.PS greeting cards:

Set 1 "special occasion" comprises:- , Happy Birthday, Time Flies, New Baby, Toot, Chin Chin.

Set 2 "everyday cheer" comprises:- Party Time, Sparkle, Smile, Thank You, Tip Top.

Each card will be printed in a different colour ink, although they may vary to those shown in the listing images. 

Handmade from lovely Italian Fabriano paper, and screenprinted in the Mr.PS studio in the northwest of England.

Free UK p&p

name: Tip Top greeting card
description:

Available in a selection of colours, each folded card comes with an orange envelope.

Size A6, blank inside for your own message, and comes protected in a cellophane sleeve.

A great gift for the pie-lover in your life, or the aspiring cook in your kitchen.

Why not add this to a hamper of gourmet goodies for a foodie gift, or how about popping it in a frame.

Free UK p&p

Also available in mustard, see separate listing. Makes a great companion to our new Happy Face mug.

Free UK p&p

description:

name: Tower tea towel
description:
This tea towel features my image of Canon Hussey Court, a residential block that I see out of my studio stairwell window.

Originally created as merchandise for the Manchester Modernist Society shop, I am re-issuing this commemorative design as the Islington Estate celebrates its Golden Anniversary this summer.

100% cotton, screenprinted in sunshine yellow. 

Size approx 45 x 75cm. Machine washable.

Comes folded in a cellophane packet.

Free UK p&p

name: Man U by Robert Shadbolt print
description:
Come on you Reds!

We are proud to present a riso print of Robert Shadbolt's illustration of Manchester United.

The first in the "Thema e Variazioni: Manchester and Salford" series, illustrator Robert Shadbolt has been making delightful drawings based on current and historical references in Greater Manchester.

Riso-printed with soya ink on recycled paper. 

Riso-printing is a similar process to screen-printing, so there are subtle variations in the surface of the print, creating a luxurious quality.

As the illustration is printed on to 120gm recycled paper, there are a few natural flecks, but this only adds to the charm.

Size: 297x300mm. Comes unframed, rolled in a postal tube for mailing. (The square frame in the photo is from Paperchase)

Signed in pencil: RS 2011

name: Robert Shadbolt riso print set - Manchester & Salford
description:
A set of four riso prints by illustrator Robert Shadbolt. 

Robert made these images as part of his ongoing "Themes & Variations" series. This set concerns his impressions of Salford and Manchester.

Each pack contains four postcard sized prints:- The Tower (teal), The Bridges (brown), Perambulator (orange), Man U (red).

100mmx 150mm, riso-printed in soya inks on recycled medium-weight card.

Riso printing is similar to screen-printing, and each card is numbered and initialed.

Postage & packaging: 
The cards come protected in a sealed cellophane sleeve, and will be sent in an envelope by first class Royal Mail. (Airmail where applicable)

Great to keep, share, send, frame.

name: Robert Shadbolt ltd ed gocco print set - Tokyo
description: Your chance to own a set of four gocco prints by illustrator Robert Shadbolt. Limited to an edition of 200, each card is numbered and initialed. Robert made these images as part of his ongoing "Themes & Variations" series. This set concerns his impressions of his recent trip to Tokyo. Each pack contains four postcard sized prints:- Godzilla Face (burgundy), Happy Faces (red), Rabbit Face (blue), Space Face (lime). 100mmx 150mm, medium-weight card, with title and details printed in silver. Gocco is a japanese printing system, similar to screenprint. Because this is a hand process, there could be some variations between each print. Postage & packaging: The cards come protected in a sealed cellophane sleeve, and will be sent in an envelope by first class Royal Mail. (Airmail where applicable) See more of Robert's work here
